    "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentswitchtracking/nssegmentswitchtrackingmomentary": {
      "title": "NSSegmentSwitchTrackingMomentary",
      "type": "topic",
      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentswitchtracking/nssegmentswitchtrackingmomentary",
      "kind": "symbol",
      "role": "symbol",
      "url": "/documentation/appkit/nssegmentswitchtracking/nssegmentswitchtrackingmomentary",
      "abstract": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "A segment is selected only when the user is pressing the mouse down within the bounds of the segment. When the mouse is no longer down within the segment, the segment is automatically deselected. A momentary segmented control sends an action when the user clicks a segment, and another action when the user releases the segment. If configured as continuous (see "
        },
        {
          "type": "reference",
          "isActive": true,
          "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscontrol/1428952-continuous"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "), the control also sends actions at repeating intervals until the user releases the segment, at which point the control sends its final action."
        }
      ]
    },
    "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentswitchtracking/nssegmentswitchtrackingmomentaryaccelerator": {
      "title": "NSSegmentSwitchTrackingMomentaryAccelerator",
      "type": "topic",
      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nssegmentswitchtracking/nssegmentswitchtrackingmomentaryaccelerator",
      "kind": "symbol",
      "role": "symbol",
      "url": "/documentation/appkit/nssegmentswitchtracking/nssegmentswitchtrackingmomentaryaccelerator",
      "abstract": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "On pressure-sensitive systems, when the user force clicks a segment, a momentary accelerator segmented control sends repeating actions as pressure changes occur. The control stops sending actions when the user releases pressure. A document-based app, for example, might implement a momentary accelerator segmented control in order to allow a user to adjust the speed of paging by using variable pressure. In this example, actions are sent to the app to indicate when pressure on the control has changed. The app then determines the amount of pressure currently applied, and adjusts navigation speed accordingly."
        }
      ]
    },
